<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-07-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-07-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="1162" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1162">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Day</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Loomis</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-07-08"><hi rend="italic">July 8,
                                1898</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 156.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                            No. 156, of the 19th ultimo, inclosing the records in the case of Felipe
                            Scandella, an American citizen, expelled from Venezuela by the
                            authorities of Ciudad Bolivar.</p>
                        <p>The Department appreciates the successful manner in which you conducted
                            the case, which you were instructed to settle in accordance with the
                            Department’s telegram of the 30th ultimo.</p>
                        <p>Respectfully, yours,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">William R. Day.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>